lawsuit?
.IP "2." 3
\f[B]Budget Compliance:\f[R] Are we distributing the limited pile of
money according to the curve?
.IP "3." 3
\f[B]Velocity:\f[R] Can we get this meeting over with?
.SS 3. The Witness Stand
In the KarmaRank chapter, we discussed Status\-Weighted Stories
(K = Σ S_i · k_i).
Here is why the variable S_i (Status) is the dominant term.
.PP
When your Manager (Attorney) presents your case, they will point to your
work.
\(lqMy report refactored the legacy billing system.\(rq
.PP
If the room is silent, that claim dies.
It is just a claim.
.PP
But if a Peer Manager (a Juror) speaks up and says: \(lqYes, and that
refactor saved my team 20 hours a week,\(rq the dynamic shifts
instantly.
.PP
\f[B]Documents do not testify.\f[R] A Jira ticket cannot take the stand.
A pull request cannot look the jury in the eye.
.PP
\f[B]People testify.\f[R]
.PP
When you help a high\-Status person in the organization, you are not
just \(lqbeing helpful.\(rq You are \f[B]securing a witness\f[R].
You are ensuring that arguments are made, you have friends in the jury
box.
.PP
This is why \(lqvisibility\(rq matters.
Visibility is simply the availability of credible witnesses during your
trial.
.SS 4. Jury Tampering as a Service
If you treat your job as \(lqwriting code,\(rq you are leaving your fate
to the rhetorical skills of your tired Manager.
.PP
If you treat your job as \(lqgenerating Status\-Weighted Stories,\(rq
you are effectively engaging in \f[B]lawful jury tampering\f[R].
.PP
Your goal is to ensure that by the time the Calibration Meeting starts,
the verdict is already technically decided because three of the five
high\-S_i people in the room have already \(lqbought\(rq your story.
.SS 5. Transitivity
Crucially, your manager is playing the same game.
They\(cqre at the bottom\-center of their Calibration Cylinder.
Their own rating will be determined by the next layer up.
Their own peers\(cq feedback funnels to their manager (your skip) whose
peers are your manager\(cqs jury.
.PP
