.SS Glossary
.SS The Laws
\f[B]Law #1: Conative Dissonance\f[R]
.PP
You are running two ledgers in one head (Private vs.
Firm).
The psychological friction experienced when these two databases drift
apart is Conative Dissonance.
.PP
\f[B]Law #2: The Rating Is The Job\f[R]
.PP
The firm does not pay you for the work; it pays you for the
\f[B]Status\-Weighted Stories\f[R] about the work.
Any effort not serialized into a rating is pro bono labor.
.PP
\f[B]Law #3: Who Cares?\f[R]
.PP
\(lqImpact\(rq is defined strictly as: \f[I]Who\f[R] (S_i)
\f[I]Cares\f[R] (k_i).
If you cannot name the specific high\-status individuals who derive
emotional value from your work, the impact is speculative.
.PP
\f[B]The Meta\-Law\f[R]
.PP
You are allowed to play the game, but you must not describe the game.
You must transubstantiate \f[B]KarmaRank\f[R] moves into HR Doxa
(\(lqbusiness impact,\(rq \(lqvalues\(rq) when speaking in public.
.SS Core Concepts
\f[B]Default Engineering Worldview (DEW)\f[R]
.PP
The vulnerable mental model that assumes meritocracy, logical
consistency, and hard work are the primary drivers of corporate success.
A legacy operating system that KarmaRank is designed to patch.
.PP
\f[B]The Firm Ledger\f[R]
.PP
The organization\(cqs accounting of value.
It does not track effort or moral virtue.
It tracks \f[B]Status\-Weighted Stories\f[R].
If an action is not recorded here, it is chemically indistinguishable
from doing nothing.
.PP
\f[B]Numerophiles\f[R]
.PP
People persuaded by numbers in the \f[B]Calibration Cylinder\f[R]
(Directors/VPs).
They are less persuaded by prose; they trust numbers and significant
digits as proxies for truth.
.PP
\f[B]The Private Ledger\f[R]
.PP
Your internal accounting of value, based on craft, ethics, and logic.
(e.g., \(lqclean code,\(rq \(lqrobust architecture\(rq).
Useful for mental health, but useless for promotion.
Do not expect the Firm Ledger to replicate data from this table.
.PP
\f[B]Red Queen\(cqs Race\f[R]
.PP
The evolutionary condition where one must constantly adapt just to
maintain current standing.
As KarmaRank tactics become popularized, the Firm will patch its
exploits (deprecating \(lqImpact\(rq), requiring you to continuously
reverse\-engineer the new board.
.PP
\f[B]Status (S_i)\f[R]
.PP
The contextual importance of a \f[I]person\f[R] (i).
Someone who sits in the calibration court has high Status.
Someone who testifies has Status transitively according to how the
evaluators in that room view them.
.PP
\f[B]Strategic Ambiguity\f[R]
.PP
A security feature of the Firm.
The intentional lack of clear, static promotion criteria to prevent
Goodhart\(cqs Law (metric gaming) and strictly retain Leadership\(cqs
veto power.
.PP
\f[B]karma (k_i)\f[R]
.PP
A synonym for \(lqaffect\(rq or \(lqcare\(rq.
How much good or bad feeling \f[I]this person\f[R] (i) has about the
subject and is willing to testify to.
.PP
\f[B]Karma (K)\f[R]
.PP
The sum of Status\-weighted karma.
(K = Σ S_i · k_i).
.PP
\f[B]Status\-Weighted Story\f[R]
.PP
The atomic unit of corporate currency.
A narrative unit featuring you, as told by someone with Status.
Stories yield karma and are weighted by the Status of the teller.
.PP
\f[B]The Uncanny Valley of Alignment\f[R]
